Various Republican representatives, including Senator David Perdue, Rep. Louie Gohmert, Rep. Jim Jordan, Rep. Dan Donovan, Rep. Mike Johnson, Rep. Earl L. "Buddy" Carter, Rep. Mark Meadows, Rep. Andy Harris, Rep. John Ratcliffe, Rep. Morgan Griffith, and Rep. Andy Biggs, express their support for President Trump's commitment to securing the U.S.-Mexico border. They highlight the importance of border security for national security, reducing illegal immigration, combating drug cartels, and enforcing the rule of law. They urge Congress to include funding for a border wall in upcoming spending bills and emphasize the need to protect the American people.